  "time_ut": 1662187760,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dad\u0db1, \u0db6\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0ddd\u0da9\u0dca\u0db6\u0dd1\u0db1\u0dca\u0da9\u0dca \u0dc4\u0dcf \u0dbb\u0dd6\u0db4\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dd3 \u0d9c\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4 \u0d89\u0dc4\u0dc5\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Telephone, broadband and TV charges are on the rise",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Telecommunication Regulatory Commission of Sri Lanka has given permission to increase all mobile and landline telephone service charges, broadband charges, pay TV service charges.",
        "The fare hike will be effective from the 5th. Accordingly, mobile and fixed phone service charges and broadband charges are to be increased by 20% and pay TV service charges are to be increased by 25%.",
        "In addition to this, the VAT increased from the last interim budget is also to be charged from the consumers."
      ],
